description:
Clinical Trial Associate (CTA) – a clinical trial associate is responsible for supporting the clinical and preclinical studies of our surgical robotic technologies. The CTA shall work closely with the company’s R&D team, and work with research nurses, nursing/surgical staffs, researchers, clinicians, and surgeons of our collaborating hospitals/universities. The CTA shall be responsible for the arrangement/organisation of clinical/pre-clinical studies, collecting data, updating/maintaining the documentations of the studies, supporting regulatory and ethical application processes, disseminating necessary information, facilitating the process of the studies and other laboratory experiments, and ensuring the compliance of quality assurance and safety guidelines.

Tasks/responsibilities

-       Support the set up and arrange of clinical/pre-clinical trials;

-       Collect and document clinical trial information in accordance with the applicable Good Clinical Practice (GCP) guidelines for clinical studies;

-       Identify needs, bottlenecks and deviation found during the studies;

-       Participate in research and development projects on request, or take on other tasks which contribute to the optimisation of the processes within the company;

-       Support the preparation of ethical and regulatory approval processes;

-       Design and perform preliminary tests prior to clinical/pre-clinical studies;

-       Record the experiments/tests/studies/trial results and generate the associated reports for internal use and for regulatory approval processes;  

-       Perform other related duties as assigned by the supervisor

Your background and profile

-       The candidate should possess a bachelor’s degree or above in biomedical engineering, medicine, medical/life sciences, clinical research management, quality management or related disciplines, with at least 3 year post-qualification experience in clinical studies, trial management or operations.

-       Experience in medical devices development or associated research/clinical studies;

-       Good communication skills of written and spoken English and Chinese;

-       Good knowledge of Good Clinical Practice (GCP) and regulations of clinical trials are necessary.

-       Excellent organisation skills

-       Excellent Computer skills

職責:

處理門診接待，協助醫生進行檢查，清洗及消毒儀器;
跟進/提醒病人覆診安排;
處理病人預約及查詢﹑登記及配藥等;
協助醫生跟症;
處理一般文書工作


要求:

中五程度或持有同等學歷;
良好粵語﹑一般英語及普通話;
懂讀寫中文及英文，具有基本電腦操作知識;
待客親切有禮﹑誠實﹑盡責﹑有工作熱誠;
具相關工作經驗者優先
地區：旺角/中環/太古

The information provided will be used for selection purpose only. All information of unsuccessful applicants will be destroyed within six months.

Clinical Trial Manager (CTM) – a clinical trial manager is responsible for the management of clinical/preclinical studies of our surgical robotic technologies. The CTM shall provide leadership in clinical/preclinical trial activities and ensure that the trials are completed within budgets, in time and with the highest quality. The CTM shall be responsible for designing the plans for the required studies, leading the associated ethical and regulatory approval processes, implementing and tracking the trial processes, overseeing the trials/studies progresses, ensuring the studies/trials are carried out in accordance with relevant regulations, collaborating with the R&D staffs of the company, and providing regular updates and reports to the senior management team of the company.

Tasks/responsibilities

-       Lead the design and set up of clinical/preclinical trials;

-       Lead the preparation of ethical and regulatory approval processes;

-       Prepare the trial protocol and generate the associated reports;

-       Design and conduct feasibility studies/experiments;

-       Manage the clinical/preclinical trial studies;

-       Design and develop the plans and budgets for clinical/preclinical studies;

-       Optimise the cost and resources to ensure that the studies are conducted according to plans and within budgets;

-       Liaise with nursing staffs, researchers, clinicians and surgeons of our collaborating hospitals and universities;

-       Design and conduct the trainings for surgical staffs/surgeons on our surgical robotic technologies;

-       Ensure compliance of staffs with the company’s operating procedures and guidelines;

-       Conduct and organise team meetings and staff training programs;

-       Collaborate with the R&D teams in the development of new robotic technologies and the arrangement of clinical/preclinical studies;

-       Provide feedback to the R&D teams on any limitations, needs and requirements found during the studies;

-       Report the progresses of the studies and plans to the company’s senior management team;



-       Participate in research and development projects on request, or take on other tasks which contribute to the optimisation of the processes within the company;

-       Perform other related duties as assigned by the supervisor;

Your background and profile

-       The candidate should possess a bachelor’s degree or above in biomedical engineering, medicine, medical/life sciences, clinical research management, quality management or related disciplines, with at least 8 year post-qualification experience and at least 3 years in clinical trial management role.

-       Extensive knowledge of regulations of clinical trials and medical device regulations;

-       Experience in medical devices development or associated research/clinical studies;

-       Excellent communication skills of written and spoken English and Chinese;

-       Excellent organisation and people management skills;

-       Excellent leadership skills;

-       Influential and assertive communication skills

工作內容:


負責抽血工作;
處理病人預約及查詢﹑登記及配藥等;
協助醫生跟症;
處理一般文書工作
要求:

中五程度或持有同等學歷;
須具備認可抽血員證書;
良好粵語﹑一般英語及普通話;
懂讀寫中文及英文，具有基本電腦操作知識;
待客親切有禮﹑誠實﹑盡責﹑有工作熱誠;
